channel.title: mycatalog updates
channel.description: 'My Catalog' uses the IBM Cloud catalog API to retrieve data from the catalog. It attempts to be as accurate as possible. This feed shows additions, updates, removals from the catalog. Use with care. It is a work-in-progress :)

item.title: [updated] Qiskit Runtime (quantum-computing) has changed the description of the plan named paygo-standard
item.description:
*before*: Systems = One 127 qubit Eagle processor and one 27 qubit Falcon processor. Time limits= program-specific up to 8 hours. Qiskit Runtime Second = time counted to process a job. No charge for job queue time. Simulators = 5 (QASM, statevector, mps, stabilizer, and extended stabilizer). Time limits = program-specific up to 3 hours., *after*: **Systems** Two systems, one 127 qubit Eagle processor and one 27 qubit Falcon processor. Time limits = program-specific up to 8 hours. Qiskit Runtime Second = time counted to process a job. No charge for job queue time.
**Simulators** Five simulators (QASM, statevector, mps, stabilizer, and extended stabilizer). Time limits = program-specific up to 3 hours.
**Performance management strategies** One strategy provided by IBM with 3 resilience levels. (Q-CTRL Embedded strategy coming soon).
